ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A survey of the development and hallmarks of medieval Russian literature -- from the end of the Cyrillo-Methodian period to the beginning of the Petrine era. I would definitely recommend to students who had the proper background in Russian and sincere interests in Russian culture.
Yes, because it is only way of getting information on pre-1800 Russia.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The course basically taught me all I know about medieval Russian literature. It made me significantly less ignorant! I am not doing a dissertation; I am a law student.
Gave me an opportunity to pass my medieval requirement in a structured way so I was not doing it alone, which would have been a very difficult task.
